				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The following works even when Windows is set to lock the workstation:<br /><br />Set a timer somewhere<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">SetTimer(hWnd, 0, 30000, NULL);<br /></div><br /><br />And in your WindowProc<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp;case WM_TIMER:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;switch (wParam)<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;{<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;case 0:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;INPUT input;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;input.type = INPUT_KEYBOARD;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;input.ki.wVk = 0x88; //Unassigned virtual keycode<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;input.ki.dwFlags = KEYEVENTF_KEYUP;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;SendInput(1, &amp;input, sizeof(INPUT));<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;return 0;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;}<br /></div><br /><br />I suppose there is some risk that your choice of keycode conflicts with some other program that's using it, but I haven't had or heard of any problems so far.</div>

					
